<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900921-0063</DOCNO><DOCID>900921-0063.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- American Credit Optical Inc.:   Firm to Buy Some Assets   Of Allied Marketing Group</HL><DATE>09/21/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   ACOI</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)ADVERTISING, MARKETING, PUBLIC RELATIONS (ADV)</IN><LP>   American Credit Optical Inc. said it signed a definitiveagreement to purchase $20 million of the operating assets ofDallas-based Allied Marketing Group Inc. The assets arerelated primarily to closely held Allied's direct mailmarketing division.   American Credit Optical, a Fort Worth, Texas, financialconcern, said the purchase is subject to financing, whichDean Witter Reynolds Inc. has been engaged to arrange. Thecompany said it expects to complete the transaction withinthe next several weeks.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>